Hello all-

Has anyone been able to build HyperNEAT on OS X Tiger (10.4.1,
specifically)? I am referring to the HyperNEAT version on the eplex page.

After a fair amount of tinkering with it, I got it to compile but now am
having troubles in the linking stage.

If someone has been able to do it, can you email me at jclune@...? I'd
love to hear how you did it, but don't want to clog up everyone's inboxes.

In case you are interested, the current error is

Linking CXX executable ../out/Hypercube_NEAT
/usr/bin/ld: can't locate file for: -lboost_thread-gcc-mt-1_33_1
collect2: ld returned 1 exit status
make[2]: *** [out/Hypercube_NEAT] Error 1
make[1]: *** [Hypercube_NEAT/CMakeFiles/Hypercube_NEAT.dir/all] Error 2
make: *** [all] Error 2

I am pretty sure what it is looking for is
libboost_thread-gcc-mt-1_33_1.dylib

But I don't have that file.

In the my_hyperneat_dir/out directory I do have

Results/           
libboost_thread-gcc-mt-1_33_1.so.1.33.1*
data/                                        libtinyxmldll.so*
dependencyAdder.cpp*                         libwx_base-2.8.so.0*
libNEAT.dylib*                               libwx_gtk2_adv-2.8.so.0*
libNEAT.so*                                  libwx_gtk2_core-2.8.so.0*
libboost_filesystem-gcc-mt-1_33_1.so.1.33.1*

I have tried a few things to try to trick it into grabbing
libboost_thread-gcc-mt-1_33_1.so.1.33.1 but no dice.

FYI: Since I don't know what the BOOST_STAGE directory should be in the
cmake file, I just made it point to my_hyperneat_dir/out to see if it would
grab these libraries.


If you have any ideas, please let me know at jclune@...

Cheers,
Jeff Clune

Digital Evolution Lab, Michigan State University
